---
source: src/tests.rs
expression: render_command_help(&refs)
---
Assert the text content of the page or an element

Usage: bl expect text [OPTIONS] <operator> <text>

Arguments:
  <operator>  Comparison: contains (substring) or equals (exact match) [possible values: contains, equals]
  <text>      Expected text or text substring

Options:
      --selector <selector>  CSS selector to scope the check to one element (defaults to full page text)
  -v, --verbose              Enable debug logging
      --headless             Hide browser window (visible by default)
      --json                 Output as JSON
  -h, --help                 Print help

Examples:
  bl expect text contains "Welcome back"
  # Pass if the page text contains it

  bl expect text equals "Logout" --selector "#nav button"
  # Pass if the element's text matches exactly
